&lt;h3 id="garden-description">Garden Description&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>A fragmentary (and probably reused) epitaph, probably of the first or second century CE, found in the catacombs of Calepodio beside the Via Aurelia identifies a cepota[phium] of Terentia.&lt;/p>
